President Obama has declared a major disaster in North Dakota due to a severe winter storm that occurred from April 1-3, 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Justo Hernandez has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and further damage assessments are conducted. For more information, contact FEMA.